      <body>
         <entry xml:id="bite-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#biz-dlgenr"
                next="#biyyah-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">ביטי</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">byṭy</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">biṭe</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="bite-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">landscape</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">core borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>cave</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>depth</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>βυθός</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     והא כת' ישובו רשעים לשאולה, ר' אבא בר זבדה אמר 
                     <app>
                        <lem>לביטי</lem> 
                        <rdg wit="#Vat1 Ox1">לדייטי</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox2">לדיטיה</rdg>
                     </app> התחתונה שבשאול.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">50,3</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 518: 5</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיטיה</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דייטי</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        The wicked shall return ‘li-sheʾolah’ – to the netherworld (Ps 9,18). Said R. Abbaʾ b. Zavdah: That means to the nethermost depth of hell. [cf. Freedman / Simon I 435)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 84 [26a: 42]</bibl>;
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 117 [36c: 11]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטי</ref>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 145 [46a: 55]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אמבטי</ref>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">YalqPs 643 [444c: 8]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטא</ref>)
         </note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     והא כת' ישובו רשעים לשאולה, ר' אבא בר זבדה אמר 
                     <app>
                        <lem>לבוטי</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">לדיוטא</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox2">לדיוטי</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K V">לאמבטי</rdg>
                     </app> התחתונה שבשאול.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">68,8</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 777: 2</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטא</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטי</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אמבטי</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        The wicked shall return ‘li-sheʾolah’ – to the netherworld (Ps 9,18). Said R. Abbaʾ b. Zavdah: That means to the nethermost depth of hell. [cf. Freedman / Simon I 435)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 84 [26a: 42]</bibl>;
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 117 [36c: 11]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטי</ref>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 145 [46a: 55]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אמבטי</ref>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">YalqPs 643 [444c: 8]</bibl> (
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוטא</ref>)
         </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.04.0057:entry=buqo/s"
                          type="entry">βυθός</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 148a</bibl> rejects this reading, correcting to
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אמבטי</ref> or
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דייטי</ref>, but cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sperber, Cards</bibl>.
       Following <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Schlatter's (1900)</bibl> suggestion for an interpretation as Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">βυθός</term>, which would represent a regular adaptation of a Greek masc. form ending in -o
in Aramaic (instead of a reconstructed (?) Greek *βέτη as suggested in the past)</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>MY II</title>
                  <citedRange>518:5</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Schlatter (1900)</title>
                  <citedRange>58</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sperber, Cards</title>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
      </body>
